This update for mozilla-nss fixes the following issues:

  - CVE-2023-0767: Fixed handling of unknown PKCS#12 safe bag types.

Vulnerabilities.Description: An attacker could construct a PKCS 12 cert bundle in such a way that could allow for arbitrary memory writes via PKCS 12 Safe Bag attributes being mishandled. This vulnerability affects Firefox < 110, Thunderbird < 102.8, and Firefox ESR < 102.8.
